cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual scene understanding from multi-view video. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions leveraging recent advances in 3D pose estimation, which is a common technique in robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions using photo-consistency, semantic and motion information for instance-level segmentation, which are all techniques commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with understanding complex dynamic scenes, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with reconstructing a detailed model of the scene.
